The First Lady of the United States, Jill Biden, spoke on National Civics Day in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. She emphasized the historical significance of Philadelphia as the birthplace of American democracy and the importance of understanding civics. Biden mentioned the Constitutional Convention held in Independence Hall where the founders created a revolutionary government that gave power to the people. She expressed gratitude towards educators, organizations, and Representative Scanlon for promoting civics education. Biden mentioned a quiz to test the students' knowledge of how the government works.